ach gives us a detailed map of the spiritual journey it triggers. This journey culminates in our apprehension of the world as a gift. And that means, in turn, that the mode of knowing appropriate to its musical ecstasy is gratitude. In the gratitude of aesthetic experience, we learn something crucial about the genuine nature of our own identity, our relations with others, and the character of the things around us. Bach’s genius lies in his capacity to frame these lessons in the mass’s choruses, solos, and duets.Spotlighting the wisdom embedded in gratitude, Bach’s Architecture of Gratitude celebrates music as a pathway to understanding our deepest selves and our intimacy with the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aGratitude. 0aMassesxAnalysis, appreciation. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Classical.2bisacsh  aAldous Huxley.  aBach.  aGadamer.  aGreek Tragedy.  aHeidegger.  aJohn Cage.  aKant.  aLeibniz.  aMass in B Minor.  aPolanyi.  aSpinoza.  aZen.  aaesthetic object.  adance.  agenius.  agratitude.  aliturgy.  aphenomenology.  aplay.  aproportion.  arhetoric.  atranscendence.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140848440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228020646?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228020646423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228020646/original  a978-3-11-140848-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles